==Adjective==
debit
# The alternate function of a debit card that uses a PIN instead of a signature, and is signified by a logo on the back of the card instead of the front (i.e., Plus, Interlink, Star vs. Visa, Mastercard, American Express, or Discover). The merchant asks if the payee wants to use "debit" or "credit", no matter which type of card they present, a "debit card" or a "credit card".